DESCRIPTION
Populate the new Producer block at capture time with the real harness identity (which adapter/runner ran, e.g. claude -p / Agent SDK), the real model that executed the stage, and the real skill version (per the source-of-truth decided in the schema bead). Wire this through the capture path (internal/cli/capture.go and the manifest writer in internal/runmanifest) so produced stages record concrete provenance rather than placeholders.

OPEN QUESTION carried from the schema bead: confirm and implement the chosen skill-version source of truth (git sha of skill repo vs SKILL.md frontmatter vs adapter-reported) — settle the exact extraction here in Plan if not fully nailed in the schema bead.

Why: an empty/placeholder producer block is useless for benches; this bead makes the captured provenance real.

Dependency: schema must land first (etude-roadmap.1.1).

DESIGN
## Plan

**Approach:** Capture is capture-side only and remains purely flag-driven (smallest change that makes provenance real). Add three new optional flags to internal/cli/capture.go — `--harness`, `--harness-version`, `--model` — and populate `Stage.Producer` (Harness{Name,Version}, Model, Skill) when building the stage. Keep `Stage.Skill` set as today so the encode-time fallback in manifest.go (toJSON: skillForProducer falls back to Stage.Skill when Producer.Skill empty) and replay/run.go keep compiling and working. No schema or Validate changes; no run-show or replay changes (those are beads 1.4 / 1.3). Back-compat is preserved: when the new flags are omitted, Harness.Name stays empty and the encoder omits the harness block exactly as 1.1 designed.

**Skill-version source of truth (settled):** FLAG-DRIVEN with a documented dogfood convention; capture.go grows NO auto-detection. Rationale, grounded in observed repo state:
- Option (a) git sha of the skill repo is unavailable here: `git -C ~/.claude/skills rev-parse HEAD` returns "not a git repository". The skills live in an unversioned dir, so shelling out would fail or require guessing the repo root — fragile, scope-creep.
- Option (b) SKILL.md frontmatter version does not exist: the dev-workflow frontmatter has only name+description (no version field). Adding+parsing frontmatter is new machinery outside this bead.
- Option (c) adapter-reported: there is no automated adapter yet (Phase 1 xenota, out of scope). Manual `etude capture` is the only producer path.
- Therefore the value MUST arrive via the existing `--skill-version` flag regardless. The real deliverable is the dogfood CONVENTION for what to pass, documented in SKILL.md (see Docs). capture.go stays flag-only.

**Files:**
- internal/cli/capture.go - add `harness`, `harnessVersion`, `model` to captureConfig; register `--harness` (default ""), `--harness-version` (default ""), `--model` (default ""); in run(), build `runmanifest.Producer{Harness: Harness{Name: cfg.harness, Version: cfg.harnessVersion}, Model: cfg.model, Skill: Skill{ID: skillID, Repo: cfg.skillRepo, Version: cfg.skillVersion}}` and set both Stage.Producer (new) and Stage.Skill (keep, unchanged) on the appended stage. No new validation; harness/model are free-form optional strings (the manifest encoder already omits empty harness/model). produced-by is a SEPARATE axis (Stage.ProducedBy, default "original") and is left untouched.
