**Exact flag -> Producer mapping:**
- `--harness <name>`     -> Producer.Harness.Name     (default "" -> harness block omitted)
- `--harness-version <v>`-> Producer.Harness.Version  (default "")
- `--model <id>`         -> Producer.Model            (default "" -> model omitted)
- `--skill-version <v>`  -> Producer.Skill.Version    (ALREADY EXISTS, default "manual")
- `--skill-id`/`--skill-repo` -> Producer.Skill.ID/Repo (already exist; Skill also still set on Stage.Skill)

**Validate decision:** KEEP harness/model OPTIONAL — do NOT newly require them. Requiring them would break every legacy/manual capture (and the existing capture tests that pass no harness/model), contradicting the 1.1 back-compat contract (empty Harness.Name -> omitted block). Stated explicitly: Validate is unchanged in this bead.

**Dogfood flag values (for SKILL.md):**
- `--harness claude-code`
- `--harness-version <Claude Code CLI version>` — convention: the running CLI version string (e.g. from `claude --version`); pass the value the orchestrator already knows for the session. Documented as "the harness/runtime version that ran the phase."
- `--model claude-opus-4-7` (the phase agents run on opus per the workflow)
- `--skill-version <skill-repo HEAD short sha OR a manual tag>` — convention: since the skills dir is not independently versioned, pass the etude repo's current `HEAD` short sha (the gate-approved artifact is tied to that commit) as the skill-version stand-in, OR a hand-set tag. Documented as a convention, not auto-resolved by capture.go.

**Tests (internal/cli/capture_test.go):**
- TestCaptureRecordsProducer: run capture with --harness claude-code --harness-version X --model claude-opus-4-7 --skill-id dev-planner --skill-version abc123; read the manifest back through ParseJSON (end-to-end through the runmanifest.Writer) and assert stage.Producer.Harness == {claude-code, X}, stage.Producer.Model == claude-opus-4-7, stage.Producer.Skill == {dev-planner, manual, abc123}, and stage.Skill mirrors it. Also assert the raw manifest.json contains a "harness" object (grep the bytes) to prove the block is emitted.
- TestCaptureOmitsHarnessWithoutFlags (back-compat): capture with NO harness/model flags; assert the run is valid (ParseJSON succeeds), stage.Producer.Harness == Harness{} (empty) and stage.Producer.Model == "", and the raw manifest.json does NOT contain "harness" (omitted block) — proving 1.1 omit-on-empty still holds through the capture path.
- Existing tests (TestCaptureCreatesRun etc.) keep passing unchanged since defaults are empty.

**Docs:**
- docs/capture.md WILL drift: the Metadata flag list and defaults block must add `--harness`, `--harness-version`, `--model` and note they are optional (omitted when empty). Flag in the Docs phase.
- .claude/skills/dev-workflow/SKILL.md "Etude Capture (Dogfood)" example + conventions list must add the three flags and the skill-version convention. Flag in the Docs phase. (Both are documentation, deferred to Docs per the five-phase flow; this Plan notes the drift so it is not missed.)

**Risks:** Low. Capture-side only, additive optional flags, no schema/Validate change, encode path for empty harness already exercised by 1.1 tests. Only judgement call is the skill-version convention, which is documentation not code.

